025,0,Creep/Slip Point
025,1,Creep Point,,Specification: 55...65 % (Moment the Vehicle starts to Move)\n\nCreep Point musst be equal or lower than the Slip Point\nDeviation from Spec. => Perform Basic Settings
; Creep Point musst be equal or lower than the Slip Point
; Deviation from Spec. => Perform Basic Settings
025,2,Slip Point,,Specification: 55...85 % (Moment the Clutch starts Slipping)\n\nSlip Point musst be equal or higher than the Creep Point\nDeviation from Spec. => Perform Basic Settings
; Slip Point musst be equal or higher than the Creep Point
; Deviation from Spec. => Perform Basic Settings
025,3,Rem. Creep Pt.,Adaptations,Specification: 0 (Deviation from Spec. => Perform Basic Settings)\n\nThe Creep Point Adaptation is performed at the End of the Basic Setting and\nhas to be repeated until the Remaing Adaptations are down to '0'.
; The Creep Point Adaptation is performed at the End of the Basic Setting and
; has to be repeated until the Remaing Adaptations are down to '0'.
025,4,Filtered,Engine Torque,Range: 0...255 (Value should be relatively constant!)\n\nDeviation (Value changes too much or jumps) => Check Engine Control Module for Fault Codes
; Deviation (Value changes too much or jumps) => Check Engine Control Module for Fault Codes
;
